definition: to deliver/to carry/to give (as a present)/to present (with)/to see off/to send

sentences.english: Work with the forwarder to ensure the goods entire on time.
sentences.chinese: 和代理公司一起確保進口及時清關及按時送貨。

sentences.english: and there' s a door on the right hand side marked deliveries.
sentences.chinese: 右手邊有個門，上面寫着送貨。

sentences.english: Delivery is free of charge within the Beijing area.
sentences.chinese: 北京市區送貨是免費的。

sentences.english: You either buy them yourself or have them delivered to your home or office.
sentences.chinese: 你可以選擇自己去購買或是送貨上門。

sentences.english: A young deliveryman disappeared after a delivery.
sentences.chinese: 一位年輕的送貨人在送貨後消失。

sentences.english: A young deliveryman disappeared after a delivery.
sentences.chinese: 一位年輕的送貨人在送貨後消失。

sentences.english: Deliverymen learned to leave things at the front door.
sentences.chinese: 送貨人都學會了把東西放在我們門口。

sentences.english: The order is marked as delivered by setting the delivery day.
sentences.chinese: 通過設置送貨日期，將訂單標記爲已發貨。

sentences.english: They deliver to within a 5-mile radius of the store.
sentences.chinese: 他們在距離商場5英里的範圍內送貨上門。

sentences.english: If you are the one, you can free shipping on any area of Yantai city.
sentences.chinese: 非誠勿擾，可以免費送貨煙臺市任何區。

sentences.english: The company's customers for the majority of ordinary express home delivery services.
sentences.chinese: 本公司爲廣大顧客提供了普通快遞送貨上門服務。

sentences.english: And have off-the-shelf direct delivery to your company.
sentences.chinese: 並且有現貨供應，可直接送貨到貴公司。

sentences.english: Delivery Service is only available when your purchase is over HK$300.
sentences.chinese: 購物必需滿港幣HK$300，方享有送貨服務。

sentences.english: Can you tell delivery people phone number?
sentences.chinese: 你能告訴送貨人的電話號碼嗎？

sentences.english: Perform on time daily pickup and delivery according to operation plan and procedures.
sentences.chinese: 根據運營規劃和程序，天天及時的取件和派送貨件。
這只是現金交易的商店，不負責送貨。

to go/take out (relates to food bought at a restaurant)
sales counter/front desk/bar/(of markets, medicines etc) OTC (over-the-counter)
